quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  28,60,"Whatever things you have been given are only the wares of the life of this world and its glitter, and what is with Allah is better and more lasting. Will you not exercise your reason"
  28,61,"Is he to whom We have given a good promise, which he will receive, like him whom We have provided the wares of the life of this world, but who will be arraigned on the Day of Resurrection"
  28,62,"The day He will call out to them and ask, ‘Where are My ‘partners’ that you used to claim?’"
  28,63,"Those against whom the word had become due will say, ‘Our Lord! These are the ones whom we have perverted. We perverted them as we were perverse ourselves. We repudiate them before You: it was not us that they worshipped.’"
  28,64,"It will be said, ‘Invoke your partners!’ So they will invoke them, but they will not respond to them, and they will sight the punishment, wishing they had followed guidance"
  28,65,"The day He will call out to them and say, ‘What response did you give to the apostles?’"
  28,66,"That day all information will be withheld from them, so they will not question one another"
  28,67,"As for him who repents, has faith and acts righteously, maybe he will be among the felicitous"
  28,68,"Your Lord creates whatever He wishes and chooses: they have no choice. Immaculate is Allah and exalted above [having] any partners that they ascribe [to Him]"
  28,69,"Your Lord knows whatever their breasts conceal, and whatever they disclose"
  28,70,"He is Allah, there is no god except Him. All praise belongs to Him in this world and the Hereafter. All judgement belongs to Him, and to Him you will be brought back"